{{for|the Bangladeshi film actress|Anwara Begum}} {{Infobox Officeholder | name = Anwara Begum | native_name = আনোয়ারা বেগম | native_name_lang = bn | office = [[Vice-Chancellor]] of [[Atish Dipankar University of Science and Technology]]
| death_date = {{death date|2018|04|21|df=y}} (aged 83) | death_place = [[Dhaka]], Bangladesh | occupation = Academic | nationality = Bangladeshi | spouse = [[Iajuddin Ahmed]] | awards = [[Ekushey Padak]] }}
'''Anwara Begum''' (died on 21 April 2018)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2018/04/22/ex-president-dr-iajuddins-wife-anwara-begum-dies/|title=Ex-president Dr Iajuddin's wife Anwara Begum dies|date=2018-04-22|work=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2018-06-07|language=en-US}}</ref> was a Bangladeshi academic. She was the first ever female to serve as a [[vice-chancellor]] of a university in Bangladesh.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://bdnews24.com/campus/2014/03/02/ju-gets-first-female-vc|title=JU gets first female VC|date=March 2, 2014|accessdate=June 26, 2016|newspaper=bdnews24.com}}</ref> In 2006, she was awarded [[Ekushey Padak]] by the [[Government of Bangladesh]] for her contribution to education.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.moca.gov.bd/site/page/c706da0c-29ee-4f0f-95d9-fa6705e19001/|title=একুশে পদকপ্রাপ্ত সুধীবৃন্দ|accessdate=June 20, 2016|publisher=Government of Bangladesh}}</ref> She was married to the 14th [[President of Bangladesh]], [[Iajuddin Ahmed]], and served as the [[First Lady of Bangladesh]] from 2002 until 2009.<ref name=munshi>{{cite news|url=http://www.munshigonj.com/BangladeshSection/President.htm|title=President|publisher=Munshigonj.com|accessdate=June 26, 2016}}</ref>
==Career== Begum was a professor of the Department of Zoology at the [[University of Dhaka]]. She later served as the chairman of the Department of Zoology and the provost of the Shamsun Nahar Hall.<ref name=munshi/>
Begum was the first chairman of the board of trustees and the founding vice-chancellor of [[Atish Dipankar University of Science and Technology]], a private university in [[Dhaka]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://varsitycampus.com/institutions/view/university/atish-dipankar-university-of-science-and-technology/?page=history|title=History|publisher=Atish Dipankar University of Science and Technology|accessdate=June 26, 2016}}</ref>
==Personal life== Begum and her husband [[Iajuddin Ahmed]] had a son, Imtiaz Ahmed Babu.
