os Zarate]] |2004–2005<ref name="White House Bio">{{cite web | url=https://georgewbush-whitehouse.archives.gov/government/jzarate-bio.html | title=Biography from the White House | publisher=The White house | accessdate=12 November 2015}}</ref> |In 2014, Zarate accepted appointment to the board that oversees the Vatican's [[Institute for the Works of Religion]], a move announced by [[George Pell|Cardinal Pell]] of the Vatican Finance Ministry as part of [[Pope Francis|Pope Francis I]]'s efforts to clean up the finances of the [[Vatican City|Vatican]].<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-07-08/pope-francis-replaces-vatican-bank-managers-as-profit-drops-97-.html | work=Bloomberg | first=Andrew | last=Frye | title=Pope Replaces Vatican Bank Managers as Profit Drops 97% | date=8 July 2014}}</ref> From 1988 to 1989 he served one term as student body president of [[Mater Dei High School (Santa Ana, California)|Mater Dei High School]] in [[Santa Ana, California]]. He was selected for the Youth Inaugural Conference which was invited to that year's inauguration of [[George H.W. Bush]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Landsbaum|first1=Mark|title=Bush Backers Caught Up in Inaugural Whirl|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1989-01-20/local/me-1249_1_george-bush/2|accessdate=29 April 2016|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=20 January 1989}}</ref> |- |}
